%U A395523 2,4,4,2,2,2,20,2,4,2,2,4,2,4,2,2,4,4,2,4,4,4
%N A395523 a(n) is the period of {F^(m) mod n} (a sequence of functions Z -> Z/nZ), where F^(m) means the m-th iteration of the Fibonacci sequence (A000045).
%C A395523 In other words, a(n) is the smallest p such that F^(m)(x) == F^(m+p)(x) (mod n) for all x and all sufficiently large m.
%C A395523 a(n) divides a(A001175(n)). Conjecture 1: a(n) = a(A001175(n)) for all n != 2 or 4.
%C A395523 If n is of the form d*5^e with d dividing 24 and e >= 1, then a(n) is divisible by 4*5^(e-1). This is because F, when viewed as a function Z/(24*5^e)Z -> Z/(24*5^e)Z, is a bijection on the set {s in Z/(24*5^e)Z : s divisible by 24 and coprime to 5} with 4*5^(e-1) elements, and so {F^(m)(12) mod n} enters a cycle of length 4*5^(e-1) for m >= 1. Conjecture 2: for such n we have a(n) = 4*5^(e-1).
%C A395523 The combination of these two conjectures implies that a(n) = 2 if A235249(n) = 24 and n != 2, 4, and a(n) = 4*5^(e-1) if A235249(n) = 24*5^e for e >= 1, where A235249(n) is the fixed point when A001175 is iterated with starting value n.
%H A395523 Jianing Song, <a href="/A395523/b395523.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A395523 Jianing Song, <a href="/A395523/a395523.txt">PARI Program</a>
%e A395523 a(7) = 2 because:
%e A395523  - {F^(2)(x) mod 7} is of period 24: {0, 1, 1, 1, 2, 5, 0, 2, 5, 1, 6, 6, 0, 6, 6, 1, 5, 2, 0, 5, 2, 1, 1, 1};
%e A395523  - {F^(3)(x) mod 7} is of period 24: {0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 5, 5, 6, 1, 6, 2, 2, 0, 2, 2, 6, 1, 6, 5, 5, 1, 1, 1, 1};
%e A395523  - for every even i >= 4, {F^(m)(x) mod 7} is of period 24: {0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 5, 1, 2, 1, 2, 6, 6, 0, 6, 6, 2, 1, 2, 1, 5, 1, 1, 1, 1};
%e A395523  - for every odd i >= 5, {F^(m)(x) mod 7} is of period 24: {0, 1, 1, 1, 1, 5, 1, 6, 1, 6, 2, 2, 0, 2, 2, 6, 1, 6, 1, 5, 1, 1, 1, 1}.
%e A395523 In conclusion, {F^(m) mod 7}, as a sequence of functions Z -> Z/7Z, has period 2.
%o A395523 (PARI) \\ See link. Note that the time complexity is O(a(n)*A001178(n)*A235249(n)) and the space complexity is O(A235249(n)).
%Y A395523 Cf. A001175, A001178, A235249.
